(1, 1, '2014-10-21 15:21:16', '2014-10-21 15:21:16', 'Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!', 'Hello world!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-world', '', '', '2014-10-21 15:21:16', '2014-10-21 15:21:16', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(2, 1, '2014-10-21 15:21:16', '2014-10-21 15:21:16', '<h1>DELIVERING THOUGHTFUL &amp; RESPONSIVE DESIGN SINCE 1968</h1>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley provides innovative architecture and integrated building consultancy operating across the UK. With over 45 years experience, our award winning team of 70 continues to successfully deliver a range of projects that transform our clients visions into reality.</p>\r\n<p>Our approach is to combine design excellence with practical expertise founded on solid commercial knowledge that ensures our projects are both realistic and achievable.</p>\r\n\r\n', 'All About Bowman Riley', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2014-11-06 07:58:44', '2014-11-06 07:58:44', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?page_id=2', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(4, 1, '2014-10-21 15:32:19', '2014-10-21 15:32:19', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\r\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pia coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\r\n...or something like this:\r\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\r\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'All About Bowman Riley', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-21 15:32:19', '2014-10-21 15:32:19', '', 2, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?p=4', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(5, 1, '2014-10-21 15:32:33', '2014-10-21 15:32:33', '', 'All About Bowman Riley', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-21 15:32:33', '2014-10-21 15:32:33', '', 2, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?p=5', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6, 1, '2014-10-21 15:34:33', '2014-10-21 15:34:33', '<h1>Our Story</h1>\r\n<p>In 1968 three architects decided to launch a new practice and unable to decide on where to locate the Head Office to best serve the commercial centres of Leeds and Manchester, a pin was stuck in a map somewhere in between. The market town Skipton, on the edge of the Yorkshire Dales was picked and there our story began.</p>\r\n<p>From the beginning the practice has had a very clear, unswerving, focus on quality design, attention to detail and client care, so much so that we continue to work with long standing clients, some of whom span back to our companys inception.</p>\r\n<p>Today Bowman Riley is a dynamic and commercial practice led by directors Darren Bush, John Coultas, Michael Feather, Matthew Jones and Laurence Teeney operating from offices in Leeds, London and Skipton. To complement our design services, we offer a range of Building Consultancy services led by Robin Holme.</p>\r\n<p>In 2010 Steve Batson and Mark Dean joined our family and launched Bowman Riley Healthcare Architects to meet the needs of this specialist market.</p>\r\n', 'Our Story', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'our-story', '', '', '2014-10-29 20:54:21', '2014-10-29 20:54:21', '', 2, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?page_id=6', 0, 'page', '', 0),
