(67, 1, '2014-08-22 14:52:50', '2014-08-22 14:52:50', '<p>The Judges Lodging hotel situated in the heart of Yorks historic city centre has recently reopened its doors following a 2.2 million major redevelopment, designed by Yorkshire based architects Bowman Riley.</p>\r\n<p>Recently purchased by Daniel Thwaites Plc, the Grade I listed Georgian townhouse closed its doors in January 2014 for a significant renovation, to reopen in July as the latest addition to the award-winning Thwaites Inns of Character collection.</p>\r\n<p>Working closely with City of York Council, English Heritage and specialist conservation groups, Bowman Riley secured consent for selective demolition works to enable the flow of the building to be replanned. A new main entrance was incorporated, which leads directly into the bar and restaurant. Extensive new dining areas were created, plus a new commercial kitchen and guest bedrooms.</p>\r\n<p>Specific challenges involved the co-ordination of extensive groundworks to avoid the medieval graveyard beneath the hotels garden courtyard and the Roman defences located below the external dining area, fronting Lendal.</p>\r\n<p>The redevelopment work has transformed The Judges Lodging to provide elegant and contemporary new bedrooms and has carefully reordered the existing facilities to create a unique experience in a historic setting.</p>\r\n<p>Built in 1726 as a private residence, The Judges Lodging was the official residence of the Assize Court Judges until the 1970s, when it was converted into a hotel.</p>\r\n<p>John Coultas, Director at Bowman Riley Architects commented:</p>\r\n<p>We are proud of our involvement in the stunning transformation of The Judges Lodging. It is a unique building with a striking contrast between the new and old, providing York with an appealing and distinctive Grade 1 Listed hotel.</p>', 'Luxury Hotel Renovated in York', 'The Judges Lodging hotel situated in the heart of Yorks historic city centre has recently reopened its doors following a 2.2 million major redevelopment, designed by Yorkshire based architects Bowman Riley.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'news-item-headline', '', '', '2014-10-29 21:18:43', '2014-10-29 21:18:43', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=news&#038;p=67', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(68, 1, '2014-08-22 14:56:44', '2014-08-22 14:56:44', '<p>Bowman Riley Architects has reached the finals for two awards at the high profile Yorkshire Business Insider Awards 2014 to be held in Leeds in September 2014.</p>\r\n<p>The company has been shortlisted in the prestigious Architecture Firm of the Year category competing and the retail development we designed at Albion Place, Skipton for Maplegrove Developments has been shortlisted for Development of the Year.</p>\r\n<p>The Awards celebrate achievements across the built environment recognising the buildings, investors, developers, architects, consultants and contractors that that make significant contributions to the ever-changing Yorkshire skyline.</p>\r\n<p>The glittering award ceremony takes place on 24 September 2014 at New Dock Hall, The Royal Armouries in Leeds.</p>', 'Shortlisted at Yorkshire Insider Property Awards 2014', 'Bowman Riley Architects has reached the finals for two awards at the high profile Yorkshire Business Insider Awards 2014 to be held in Leeds in September 2014.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'news-item-headline-2', '', '', '2014-10-29 21:05:06', '2014-10-29 21:05:06', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=news&#038;p=68', 0, 'news', '', 0),
