(349, 1, '2014-10-29 19:26:01', '2014-10-29 19:26:01', '<h1>Augmented Reality</h1>\r\n<p>At Bowman Riley, we are exploring how the use of augmented reality and wider interactive digital technologies can provide our clients with a new way of visualising their building projects.<br /> In a virtual reality computer simulated environment, a project can be walked around and interacted with in context to its vicinity and surroundings.</p>\r\n<p>A tablet or smart phone can be pointed at a QR code on a computer generated rendered image or physical model of a project to show a 3D to scale, 360o view.</p>\r\n<p>As architects, we are investigating how augmented reality will affect how we design buildings in the future.We have used augmented reality in a large master planning project for a manufacturer sector, for Team Skys Office Pod and for a specialist equipment manufacturer.</p>', 'Augmented Reality', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'augmented-reality', '', '', '2014-11-04 06:39:47', '2014-11-04 06:39:47', '', 338, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?page_id=349', 5, 'page', '', 0),
