(504, 1, '2014-10-30 11:02:45', '2014-10-30 11:02:45', '<h3>DTZ</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Architects was commissioned to provide masterplanning and feasibility services on behalf of the Homes and Communities Agency, Department for Communities and Local Government and Walsall Council to examine the development potential of sites across Walsall and Wolverhampton as part of the Governments Enterprise Zone Initiative.</p>\r\n<p>We produced detailed site plans for seven of the areas identified by the Council; all of which had difficult and limiting factors such as services easements, contamination or unstable ground. Phoenix 10, the largest of the sites, is reported to be the most contaminated site in Europe and without the Enterprise Zone, funding would never be commercially viable for industrial redevelopment.</p>\r\n<p>Working alongside DTZ, the sites were evaluated and a range of industrial units from large scale distribution warehouses to bespoke innovate hybrid commercial / office units were proposed. The intention is to maximise developable area within the Enterprise Zone boundaries to take advantage of the maximum funding contribution.</p>\r\n<p>We were able to provide quick turn-around response times for drawing production and amendments to facilitate the delivery of clear and concise strategies, which benefitted the wider team in their respective roles.</p>', 'Walsall Enterprise Zone', 'Bowman Riley Architects was commissioned to provide masterplanning and feasibility services on behalf of the Homes and Communities Agency, Department for Communities and Local Government and Walsall Council to examine the development potential of sites across Walsall and Wolverhampton as part of the Governments Enterprise Zone Initiative.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dtz', '', '', '2014-11-04 15:11:11', '2014-11-04 15:11:11', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=504', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
(505, 1, '2014-10-30 11:02:40', '2014-10-30 11:02:40', '', 'Walsall-Enterprise-Zone-1200x800', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'walsall-enterprise-zone-1200x800', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:02:40', '2014-10-30 11:02:40', '', 504, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Walsall-Enterprise-Zone-1200x800.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(506, 1, '2014-10-30 11:05:40', '2014-10-30 11:05:40', '<h3>Karnataka Institute of Diabetology</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was invited to lead an international team to design a state of the art 250 bed hospital for the Institute Karnataka Institute of Diabetology.</p>\r\n<p>Diabetes is a major health issue in India with over 30 million people diagnosed with the condition, the highest number of diabetics in any country in the entire world.</p>\r\n<p>Our proposals for the new hospital was for a 25,000 m2 building designed to accommodate an in-patient ward tower with panoramic views over Bangalore, outpatient block, clinical zone, staff residential building, food court and modern convention centre befitting the countrys leading specialist hospital.</p>\r\n<p>Bowman Rileys approach was to clearly define public and non-public areas with an airport style covered concourse with links to the out-patient and clinical zone to provide a quality modern 21st century health hotel facility. At the heart of our design, we integrated landscaping and therapeutic gardens offering patients, staff and visitors a quality external environment.</p>\r\n<p>Our proposal was for the hospital to be designed to the latest international health design standards using the TAHPI, Health Facility Briefing System (HFBS India).</p>\r\n<p>Our highly sustainable design was to LEED environmental standards with a state of the art energy centre. The mass of the concrete structure would be used to absorb the daytime heat to limit internal temperatures without the need for air conditioning.</p>', 'Karnataka Institute of Diabetology', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was invited to lead an international team to design a state of the art 250 bed hospital for the Institute Karnataka Institute of Diabetology.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'karnataka-institute-diabetology', '', '', '2014-10-30 13:55:19', '2014-10-30 13:55:19', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=506', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
(507, 1, '2014-10-30 11:05:35', '2014-10-30 11:05:35', '', 'Knarnataka-Institute-of-Diabetology', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'knarnataka-institute-of-diabetology', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:05:35', '2014-10-30 11:05:35', '', 506, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Knarnataka-Institute-of-Diabetology.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(508, 1, '2014-10-30 11:07:32', '2014-10-30 11:07:32', '<h3>TB Hospital, Swaziland</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare Architects donated their time and expertise on a pro bono basis to design the refurbishment of the Good Shepherd Hospital, National TB Hospital in Swazilands commercial hub, Manzini following incidences of multi drug-resistant tuberculosis infecting healthcare workers.</p>\r\n<p>TB is one of the primary killers in Swaziland and the main opportunistic disease in people living with HIV and AIDS. Working in collaboration with Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, the University of Leeds and Apex4D, a low tech, low cost solution to this 21st century problem aimed at improving infection control measures.</p>\r\n<p>We redesigned the internal layout and the air flow at the hospital to control the spread of this airborne highly infectious disease. The nurses station was relocated and enclosed from the hospital wards to reduce exposure to the disease and natural ventilation was introduced to manage the air flow regime.</p>\r\n<p>Our work was undertaken using Building Information Modelling (BIM) software and Revit Architecture to provide a 3D model and simulate the site, which enabled us to model the refurbishment from the UK without the need to survey the hospital in person.</p>\r\n<p>Over and above using BIM as a design tool, the model will be used by the University of Leeds to further research into the spread of airborne pathogens and the effectiveness of control devices.</p>', 'Good Shepherd Hospital, National TB Hospital', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare Architects donated their time and expertise on a pro bono basis to design the refurbishment of the Good Shepherd Hospital, National TB Hospital in Swazilands commercial hub, Manzini following incidences of multi drug-resistant tuberculosis infecting healthcare workers.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'good-shepherd-hospital-national-tb-hospital', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:07:32', '2014-10-30 11:07:32', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=508', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
(509, 1, '2014-10-30 11:07:28', '2014-10-30 11:07:28', '', 'TB-Hospital-Swaziland', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'tb-hospital-swaziland', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:07:28', '2014-10-30 11:07:28', '', 508, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/TB-Hospital-Swaziland.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(510, 1, '2014-10-30 11:12:08', '2014-10-30 11:12:08', '<h3>Furze Hill Court Extra Care Development</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare Architects was commissioned by the Maria Mallaband Care Group, one of the UKs leading care home providers to deliver an exclusive development of 11 luxury two- bedroom retirement extra care apartments for the over 55s situated adjacent to Furze Hill Lodge Care Home.</p>\r\n<p>The retirement apartments were designed to provide stylish and contemporary living with peace of mind and security with private patio gardens set in the grounds of the picturesque Surrey village of Kingswood.</p>\r\n<p>The apartments in Kingswood provide extra care facilities as a genuine alternative to a traditional care home environment for those who wish to pursue a more independent lifestyle, but still have access to care as and when it is needed.</p>\r\n<p>Images courtesy of Maria Mallaband Care Group.</p>', 'Maria Mallaband Care Group', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare Architects was commissioned by the Maria Mallaband Care Group, one of the UKs leading care home providers to deliver an exclusive development of 11 luxury two- bedroom retirement extra care apartments for the over 55s situated adjacent to Furze Hill Lodge Care Home.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'maria-mallaband-care-group', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:12:08', '2014-10-30 11:12:08', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=510', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
