(512, 1, '2014-10-30 11:13:58', '2014-10-30 11:13:58', '<h3>Russell House Residential Care Development</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design and develop planning information and the working drawing package on Russell House, a new build residential care development in Ampthill.</p>\r\n<p>The 64 bedroom care home for older people forms part of a wider development including high quality, low density houses.</p>\r\n<p>Set in a conservation area, the care home complements existing buildings on the site in terms of scale, massing and built form with two L shaped blocks around two secure walled gardens with views into the gardens from the dining areas.</p>\r\n<p>Each block is based on 10 -15 are clustered around nurse base hubs. The day spaces including a semi-hexagonal conservatory and dining areas are located around the development providing smaller, non-institutional style spaces.</p>', 'Campbell Buchanan', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design and develop planning information and the working drawing package on Russell House, a new build residential care development in Ampthill.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'campbell-buchanan', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:13:58', '2014-10-30 11:13:58', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=512', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
