(514, 1, '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '<h3>Autistic Care Development</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new 24 bedroom autistic care development with communal facilities, car parking and landscaping to provide facilities for supported living for people with autism.</p>\r\n<p>Our design seeks to create a secure and welcoming development comprising a single storey six bedroom home and two four bedroom homes and a two storey apartment building with 10 flats. The emphasis was on creating a sense of place and a space that is intimate.</p>\r\n<p>The arrangements and massing of the buildings has been designed to minimise the impact on the surrounding neighbourhood. Corresponding with the triangular shape of the of the site, the buildings have been arranged with single storey bungalows to the south and east with the taller building located centrally. Hipped roofs reduce the skyline impact of the building and assist in visually stepping down towards the boundaries.</p>\r\n<p>Due to the nature of the building, inclusive access was of primary importance. The building has been designed to be accessible throughout for residents and visitors.</p>', 'Autism Care UK (part of the Maria Mallaband Care Group)', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new 24 bedroom autistic care development with communal facilities, car parking and landscaping to provide facilities for supported living for people with autism.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'autism-care-uk-part-maria-mallaband-care-group', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '2014-10-30 11:16:02', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=514', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
