(516, 1, '2014-10-30 11:17:51', '2014-10-30 11:17:51', '<h3>Buckingham House Care Home</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to develop the designs for a new luxurious residential care home to accommodate 53 older people in a conservation area within the village of Gerrards Cross.</p>\r\n<p>The new residence provides residential, nursing and dementia care on the site of a redundant public house that had been closed since 2007.</p>\r\n<p>The design incorporates three distinct design elements. The south-eastern block reflects the design of the former public house building whilst the north-western block mirrors the traditional local vernacular. A modern glazed element links the two, with a large modern element to the rear of the buildings. The result is that the building appears to have developed organically on site.</p>\r\n<p>There are several listed buildings in the vicinity of the site and it was important that the new building does not detract from the conservation area setting.</p>\r\n<p>The design was produced using Building Information Modelling (BIM) and Revit Architecture. The use of BIM helped develop the complex scheme considering the unusually shaped site and the restrictions placed its redevelopment.</p>', 'Maria Mallaband Care Group', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to develop the designs for a new luxurious residential care home to accommodate 53 older people in a conservation area within the village of Gerrards Cross.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'maria-mallaband-care-group-2', '', '', '2014-10-30 13:55:00', '2014-10-30 13:55:00', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=516', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
