(527, 1, '2014-10-30 11:30:11', '2014-10-30 11:30:11', '<h3>Pharmacy Development</h3>\r\n<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new pharmacy development comprising both pharmacy and office accommodation in addition to communal facilities, car parking and landscaping.</p>\r\n<p>Located at the junction of Frank Street and Belgrave Middleway in Birmingham city centre, the site presented several challenges including an easement line which runs diagonally across the site for future highways improvements and a three metre height difference between the southwest and northeast boundaries.</p>\r\n<p>Similar to existing buildings in the area, the new building is arranged over two storeys with a flat roof and consists of red brick, painted render and timber cladding. Curtain walling and spandrel infill panels frame the retail space and office above to define the main entrance while a sloping roof projects overhead to provide the local community with a new landmark.</p>', 'MEJ Hingley & Co Ltd', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare was commissioned to design a new pharmacy development comprising both pharmacy and office accommodation in addition to communal facilities, car parking and landscaping.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mej-hingley-co-ltd', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:30:11', '2014-10-30 11:30:11', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=casestudies&#038;p=527', 0, 'casestudies', '', 0),
