(531, 1, '2014-10-29 11:33:59', '2014-10-29 11:33:59', '<p>Bowman Riley Healthcare formed part of the team involved in the refurbishment of a TB Hospital in Swaziland, which has just won the IHEEM Northcroft Silver Medal for Outstanding Contribution to the Advancement of Healthcare Engineering!</p>\r\n<p>We donated our time on a pro bono basis to design the refurbishment of the Good Shepherd Hospital following incidences of drug-resistant tuberculosis infecting healthcare workers.</p>\r\n<p>Working in collaboration with Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, the University of Leeds and Apex4D, a low tech, low cost solution was introduced to this 21st century problem aimed at improving infection control.</p>\r\n<p>We redesigned the layout and the air flow at the hospital to control the spread of this airborne highly infectious disease.</p>\r\n<p>Our work was undertaken using Building Information Modelling (BIM) software to provide a 3D model and simulate the site, which enabled us to model the refurbishment from the UK without the need to survey the hospital in person.</p>', ' Infection Control in a Developing World ', 'Bowman Riley Healthcare formed part of the team involved in the refurbishment of a TB Hospital in Swaziland, which has just won the IHEEM Northcroft Silver Medal for Outstanding Contribution to the Advancement of Healthcare Engineering!', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'infection-control-developing-world', '', '', '2014-10-30 11:35:02', '2014-10-30 11:35:02', '', 0, 'http://92.60.114.159/~bowmanriley/?post_type=news&#038;p=531', 0, 'news', '', 0),
